@NODE what "What is Blitz-Check?"

Blitz-Check is a new file upload checker for DLG. Some of its features are:

       o Can be configured for an UNLIMITED number of archivers.
       o Checks file integrity.
       o @{"Removes an UNLIMITED number of junk files from the archive" link workdel}.
       o Extracts FILE_ID.DIZ file from archive.
       o Informs the sysop of all private uploads which occur.
       o Allows the sysop to @{"skip files" link skip} (eg: BlitzTag.TXT)

Whats to be added:

       o Hopefully virus checking using virus_Checker
       o Other features, as they are requested, if possible

@ENDNODE
@NODE Setup "Setting up Blitz-Check"

Blitz-Check relies on a @{"config file" link config} for its operations. The config file is
called 'DLGConfig:Misc/Blitz-Check.cfg', and stores the sysop name and the
archiver types.

To run Blitz-Check, place an entry into your 'DLGConfig:Batch/UPLOAD1.Batch'
file, calling Blitz-Check thus:

       Blitz-Check {username} {filename} [WORKDIZ] [WORKDEL] [LOGALL]

The 3 optional parameters are:

       WORKDIZ - Attempt to extract FILE_ID.DIZ to use as description.
       @{"WORKDEL" link workdel} - Attempt to remove junk files from the archive.
       LOGALL  - Inform the sysop of every upload, not just private uploads.

Blitz-Check is now ready to be run.
@ENDNODE
@NODE workdel "Blitz-Check's junk deleter"

Blitz-Check allows you to delete any number of files from the uploaded file.

To do this, it uses a file to get the list of files. The file is called
'DLGConfig:Misc/Blitz-Check.DEL'. It has a simple form, but it does need some
explanation.

Each line in this file is passed to the archive program, unaltered.

IMPORTANT: If a file has spaces in it, you MUST put quotes around it!

The way the line is passed allows you to put more than 1 file on each line.
This will speed up the process, but you need to make sure that all archive
programs can handle multiple files in one calling.

See the included file for an example of this file.

I have encountered a problem where-by certain files are not removed. I am
still to figure out why.

@ENDNODE
@NODE skip "File skipping"

Blitz-Check now allows you to skip files which have been uploaded. This may
be of use for certain files which get uploaded often.

Blitz-Check will read a file called 'DLGConfig:Misc/Blitz-Check.Skip', and
has 1 file per line.

@ENDNODE
@NODE config "Blitz-Check's config file"

       Line 1: The sysop's name.

From here on, lines are grouped in groups of 5:

       Line 2: Extension to test. Eg: .LHA
       Line 3: Command to test integrity of archive.
       Line 4: Command to extract file from archive.
       Line 5: Command to delete files from archive.
       Line 6: Result code returned by archiver upon an integrity test FAIL.

Please see the enclosed config file for an example.

Important: Because some archiver's don't offer a delete option, or even a
           file extract option, if you place the word 'NONE' in the config
           file, then the operation won't be attempted.

@ENDNODE
@NODE status "Program status"

Blitz-Check is part of the Blitz-Utils package.

In the shareware version, only the integrity checker will work, unless you
have an access level of 255. This is to allow the sysop to have a look at the
program as if it were registered.

       Blitz-Utils includes:

       o Blitz-Upload - A GUI driven file uploader for DLG.
       o Blitz-User   - A GUI driven user editor for DLG.
       o Blitz-Twit   - A TWIT handler and a security checker.
       o Blitz-Batch  - Add files to user's batch list easily.

       The cost is US$20, or US$15 if you have registered the M-Tag package, or
register it at the same time as you register any of my other programs.

       This gets you the Blitz-Utils keyfile, which unlocks all programs in the
Blitz-Utils suite.

       When you register, place your keyfile in DLGConfig:Misc/

@ENDNODE
